section.def:
Administration
                (主管當局) means the Government of the state whose
            flag the ship is flying;

amidships
                (船舯) means the mid point of the length (as
            defined below);

Convention
                (公約) means the International Convention on
            Tonnage Measurement of Ships, 1969;

subparagraph.def:
weathertight
                            (風雨密) means that in any sea
                        conditions water will not penetrate into the ship;

paragraph.content:
for ships assigned load lines in accordance with the Load Line Rules, the
                    draught corresponding to the Summer Load Line (other than timber load
                    lines);

assembly of that ship has commenced comprising at least 50 tonnes or 1 per
                    cent of the estimated mass of all structural material whichever is the
                    less;

section.def:
surveyor
                (驗船師) means a surveyor appointed by a Certifying
            Authority;

trawler
                (拖網漁船) has the meaning assigned to it in
                section 91 of the Merchant Shipping Ordinance (Cap. 281);

paragraph.content:
existing ships to which regulation 13(1) of these regulations
                    would otherwise apply but which undergo alterations or modifications which
                    result in a substantial variation in their existing gross tonnage;

tr.td:
N1 and
                                N2 shall be taken as zero when
                                N1 + N2 is less than 13;

paragraph.content:
engineers’ storerooms and workshops not exceeding in total tonnage
                    3/4
                    of 1 per cent of the gross tonnage of the ship;

def.continued:
and shall also include framed-in spaces on or
                above the upper deck described in paragraph 4(1)(e) and included in the
                gross tonnage of the ship in accordance with that provision;

paragraph.content:
its register tonnage and the deductions and allowances made
                            pursuant to paragraphs 10 and 11 respectively in
                            ascertaining that tonnage;

the underdeck tonnage of the ship ascertained in accordance with
                            the provisions of paragraph 5 and paragraph 1 of
                            Rule I of Appendix 1 to this Schedule;

the tonnage of between deck space between the second deck and the
                            upper deck ascertained in accordance with the provisions of
                                paragraph 2 of the said Rule I;

subparagraph.content:
the tonnage of framed-in spaces on or above the upper deck
                                which contain any part of the propelling machinery or which light or
                                ventilate space appropriated for such machinery;

paragraph.content:
the tonnage of hatchways described in paragraph 6,
                            ascertained in accordance with the provisions of that paragraph and
                                paragraph 5 of the said Rule I;

subparagraph.content:
the owner of the ship has made written application to the
                                Certifying Authority for the inclusion of such spaces in the
                                propelling machinery space of the ship;

paragraph.content:
a passage way at the ship’s side, unless it is 4 feet wide or
                                more and is completely open to the weather at one end, or both ends,
                                of its length;

companions and access hatches serving as protection for stairways or
                        ladderways leading to space below, and openings over such stairways and
                        ladderways;

the galley, and any separate bakery fitted with ovens, provided in
                        either case that no part thereof is appropriated for use for any other
                        purpose;

workshops and storerooms appropriated for the use of pumpmen,
                        engineers, electricians, carpenters and boatswains, and the
                        lamp-room;

shelter space providing weather protection only for use, free of
                        charge, by deck passengers in ships intended for use only on voyages not
                        exceeding 10 hours duration;

there has been no change since the date on which the tonnage of the
                            ship was last measured in the purpose for which the space is used;
                            and

space occupied by the donkey engine and boiler if they are outside the
                        propelling machinery space and connected to the main pumps of the
                        ship;

subparagraph.content:
if the tonnage of the propelling machinery space is 13 per cent or
                            over but less than 20 per cent of the gross tonnage the allowance shall
                            be 32 per cent of the gross tonnage;

if the tonnage of the propelling machinery space is 20 per cent or
                            over but less than 30 per cent of the gross tonnage the allowance shall
                            be 37 per cent of the gross tonnage;

paragraph.content:
if taken at the level of the top of an open floor, exceed the
                                maximum height of open floor applicable to the ship obtained by
                                reference to columns A and B of Table I;

the product of multiplying together its overall length, breadth
                                and depth, and multiplying the resultant figure by 0.0045;
